---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="About — JPX Web Development Co."
  description="Full-stack developer building websites and web applications for small businesses and nonprofits."
>
  <div class="max-w-[640px] mx-auto px-8 pt-16 pb-24">
    <span class="eyebrow mb-4">About</span>
    <h1 class="text-[36px] md:text-[46px] mt-4 mb-6">Hi, I'm Ethan — I run JPX Web Development Co.</h1>

    <div class="prose-case mt-8">
      <p>
        JPX is me: a full-stack developer who builds websites and web applications for small businesses and
        nonprofits — not templated marketing pages, but the actual infrastructure underneath: registration flows,
        admin dashboards, the unglamorous plumbing that makes an organization's day-to-day actually work.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is a fair example of how I work. I designed and built every part of it myself — the glass panels,
        the sliders on the In The Beginning card, the whole visual system — the same way I approach a client
        project: figure out exactly what it needs to do, then build it properly instead of reaching for a template.
      </p>
      <p>
        I work directly with the people I build for. No account managers, no outsourced backend, no handoff between
        "the developer" and "the person you actually talk to" — just one person who writes the code, tests it, and
        answers the phone after launch. If a project isn't a good fit, I'll tell you that upfront instead of taking
        it anyway.
      </p>
      <p>
        Small businesses and nonprofits get the same rate, the same code quality, and the same attention — I don't
        treat one as charity work and the other as the "real" job.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 flex items-center gap-5">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-neu inline-block">Book a 20-min call</a>
      <a class="link-ghost" href="/#work">See the work <span class="arr">→</span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
